<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="754" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-21"><hi rend="italic">January 21,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. McCormick states that the respective dossiers from Vladivostok, upon
                            which the decisions rendered by the admiralty court are based, can
                            furnish the Department with any detailed information. Asks whether he is
                            to procure and forward translations.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>